## using the UMAP embedding and majority clusters, relabel the MSN subtypes
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3 = obj_msn$celltype2

## the bad cluster
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(8, 12, 16:18)] = 'Drop'

## matrix neurons
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(1, 3, 5, 9)] = 'D1-Matrix'
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(0, 2, 4, 10, 15)] = 'D2-Matrix'

## striosome neurons
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(7, 14)] = 'D1-Striosome'
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(6, 13)] = 'D2-Striosome'

## special child
obj_msn@meta.data$celltype3[obj_msn$seurat_clusters %in% c(11)] = 'D1/D2-Hybrid'

## visualize the cluster assignments
DimPlot(obj_msn, reduction = "umap", group.by = "celltype3", label = TRUE, label.size = 10, 
                cols = ArchR::paletteDiscrete(unique(obj_msn$celltype3)))

In [30]:
## using the UMAP embedding and majority clusters, relabel the rest of the cell types
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3 = obj_merged$celltype2

## the neurons
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3 = obj_msn[['celltype3']][colnames(obj_merged),]
# obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(27, 30, 29)] = 'Interneurons'
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3 = with(obj_merged[[]], ifelse(
    obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(27, 30, 29) & is.na(celltype3), 'Interneurons', ifelse(
    !is.na(celltype3), celltype3, NA )))

## the glia
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(5, 13, 33)] = 'Astrocytes'
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(35, 32)] = 'Endothelial'

obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(0:4, 7:9, 11, 15)] = 'Oligos'
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(6, 17)] = 'Oligos_Pre'

obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(10, 18, 23)] = 'Microglia'
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(34)] = 'Mural'

## the bad clusters
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[obj_merged$seurat_clusters %in% c(21, 28, 37, 36, 26, 19)] = 'Drop'
obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3[is.na(obj_merged@meta.data$celltype3)] = 'Drop'

## visualize the cluster assignments
DimPlot(obj_merged, reduction = "umap", group.by = "celltype3", label = TRUE, label.size = 8, 
                cols = ArchR::paletteDiscrete(unique(obj_merged$celltype3)))

# 5) subset the inter neurons, subcluster, and annotate
obj_int = obj_merged %>% 
  subset(subset = celltype1 == 'Interneurons') %>% 
  RunPCA(verbose = FALSE) %>% 
  FindNeighbors(dims = 1:30, verbose = FALSE) %>%
  RunUMAP(dims = 1:30, verbose = FALSE) %>% 
  FindClusters(resolution = 0.1, algorithm = 2,verbose = FALSE)
